{"body": "What's it consistent with?\r\n\r\nMap yields each element to a block and returns an array of the results. Map with `&:attr` would call `attr` on all those records. But now map with `:attr` would return raw column values, having not iterated over the records at all, or called the `attr` method, which may be overridden.\r\n\r\nThis could make sense on the relation itself, but that's just `project`.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2348833", "created_at": "2011-10-10T15:55:18Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1915#issuecomment-2348833", "updated_at": "2011-10-10T15:55:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1915, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jeremy", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F84d9ee44e457ddef7f2c4f25dc8fa865.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/received_events", "gravatar_id": "24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jeremy", "type": "User", "id": 199, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523fea5cbd354364b901c5af"}, "id": 2348833, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1915"}
